an-S01928.png\"></li>\n        </ul>\n        <hr>\n        <h3><span></span> Liushutong characters (2)</h3>\n        <ul class=\"list-inline list-unstyled\">\n          <li class=\"text-center\"><img src=\"hanziyan-L38349.png\"></li>\n        </ul>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"two_children__horiz_even\">\n  <div id=\"yw11\">\n    <h4><span>谥</span>字的基本解释</h4>\n    <div>\n      <p>谥<br>（謚）<br>shì<br>古代帝王或大官死后评给的称号：谥号。谥法。谥宝（帝王陵墓中，刻有帝后谥号的印玺）。<br>叫作，称为：“身死无名，谥为至愚”。<br><br></p>\n    </div>\n    <div><span>谥</span>字的汉语字典释义</div>\n    <div>\n      <p>[①]［shì］<br>［《廣韻》神至切，去至，船。］<br>亦作“諡1”。“谥1”的繁体字。<br>(1)古代帝王、贵族、大臣、士大夫或其他有地位的人死后，据其生前业迹评定的带有褒贬意义的称号。亦指按上述情况评定这种称号。<br>(2)称；号。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div><span>谥</span>字的康熙字典解释</div>\n    <div>\n      <p>【酉集上】【言字部】　謚； 康熙笔画：16； 页码：<a href=\"https://images.yw11.com/kangxi/1188.gif\" target=\"_blank\"><span>页1188第18</span></a><br>【唐韻】【集韻】?伊昔切，音益。【說文】笑貌。　又【集韻】馨激切，音鬩。笑聲。或作赥。　【正字通】俗用爲誄行之諡，非。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div><span>谥</span>字的源字形</div>\n    <div>\n      <h3>字源演变：</h3><span><span><img src=\"yw11-zixing-8C25.gif\">小篆</span><span><img src=\"yw11-zixing-8C25.gif\">楷体</span></span>\n      <h3>字形对比：</h3><span><span><img src=\"yw11-zixing-8C25.gif\">中国大陆宋体</span><span><img src=\"yw11-zixing-8C25.gif\">台湾细明体</span><span><img src=\"yw11-zixing-8C25.gif\">韩国明朝体</span><span><img src=\"yw11-zixing-8C25.gif\">旧字形</span></span>\n    </div>\n    <div><span>谥</span>字的起名意思</div>\n    <div>\n      <p>古代帝王或大官死后评给的称号；授与，加封。</p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <div id=\"yw11_en_transl\">posthumous title<br>Basic explanation of words<br>posthumous title<br>(posthumous title)<br>shì<br>The title given to an ancient emperor or high official after his death: posthumous posthumous title. Posthumous law. Posthumous treasure (in the tomb of the emperor, the seal of the posthumous posthumous name of the emperor is engraved).<br>It is called, called: \"Death is nameless, posthumous posthumous stupidity\".<br>posthumous title<br>Chinese dictionary definition of words<br>[①]［shì］<br>[\"Guangyun\" God is cut, go to, ship. ]<br>Also known as \"posthumous 1\". Traditional characters for \"谥1\".<br>(1) After the death of ancient emperors, nobles, ministers, scholar-officials, or other persons with status, titles with commendatory and derogatory significance were assessed according to their deeds during their lifetime. It also refers to the evaluation of this title according to the above circumstances.<br>(2) Title; number.<br>posthumous title<br>Kangxi dictionary interpretation of words<br>[You Ji 1] [Words Department] 　谥; Kangxi strokes: 16; Page number: page 1188 to 18<br>[Tang Yun] [Ji Yun]? Ixiqie, Yinyi. [Said the text] Smile.　[Jiyun] Xin is excited, and the sound is awkward. laughter. Or make a fuss.　【Zhengzitong】It is commonly used as a posthumous posthumous posthumous title, not.<br>posthumous title<br>Source glyph<br>Character evolution: Xiaozhuan<br>Italics<br>Font comparison: Song Ti, Mainland China<br>Taiwan Minutes<br>Korean Ming Dynasty<br>Old glyph<br>posthumous title<br>Name meaning<br>The title given by an ancient emperor or high official after his death; granted and sealed.</div>\n</div>\n<div></div>\n<hr>\n<div id=\"bkrs_pinyin\">shì</div>\n<div id=\"bkrs_transl\">\n  <div>посмертное почётное имя, посмертный титул</div>\n  <div><span class=\"example-item\">有武功的谥为武 тем, кто имел военные заслуги, жалуют посмертный титул (почётное имя) «Воинственный»</span></div>\n</div>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mdbg.net/chinese/dictionary?page=worddict&wdrst=0&wdqtm=0&wdqcham=1&wdqt=\">MDBG</a> | <a href=\"https://bkrs.info/slovo.php?ch=谥\">BKRS</a> | <a href=\"https://dictionary.writtenchinese.com/#sk=谥&svt=pinyin\">WriCh</a> | <a href=\"http://www.qianyix.com/words/index.php?q=谥\">Qianyix</a> | <a href=\"https://www.yellowbridge.com/chinese/sentsearch.php?word=谥\">YBridge</a> | <a href=\"http://cca.xingtanlu.cn/?action=page&pid=8&do=search&name=谥\">Collocs</a> | <a href=\"https://characterpop.com/exp